						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But I imagine that unless the system uses a separate chip for each bit plane, it's easier to design systems whose bit depth is a power of two.</div><br />Not necessarily, the whole point of planar arrangement is that it makes arbitrary bit depths much easier (power of two or not). Available die space (to cache the pixels) is probably a bigger deal in this case.</div>

