						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Namco's 288x224 pixel boards use a 6.144 MHz pixel clock, which is very close to true square pixels (about 1/800 off the 945/154 = 6.136 MHz clock implied by Rec. 601).</div><br />I'm surprised. I'd expect 320px horizontally to yield square pixels, as 240 * 4:3 = 320. Guess I was wrong.<br /><br />If I ever do what I mention in the title I'll probably use 256x224 in order to convert it easily from the NES, but I could also use 384x224 and scale everything horizontally times 1.5 (my 32x32 metatiles would become 48x32). Other resolutions would be impratical and require significant modifications of game levels, or very strange metatile sizes such as 40x32 (320 px horizontally).</div>

